<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM WAR</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 19 15:08:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hi, to all veterans and non-veterans.  I am a student researcher on the Vietnam War. I am currently doing interviews of War Veterans and Non-veterans. For those that can spare a few minutes to answer the following questions, Thank You!<br><br>
Non-Veterans<br>
1. What is your name and what did you do during the war?<br>
2. What do you remember about your feelings concerning the U.S. involvement? Waht did you think was the purpose of the U.S. in Vietnam?<br>
3. What were your views on Vietnam? Have the changed with time?<br>
4. What vivid memories do you have about this period?<br>
5. Now have your views changed since 1973?<br>
6. What lessons do you think U.S. learned?<br><br>
Veterans<br>
1. What is your name and what was your position in Vietnam?<br>
2. What were your feelings hen you found out you had to go to Vietnam? Why did you think you had to go?<br>
3. What vivd memories do you have?<br>
4. Did these experience change your views on Vietnam?<br>
5. How were you treated by friends and family when you got home?<br>
6. Now, how do you view your service in Vietnam?<br>
7. What lessons do you think the U.S. learned?<br><br>
                           Once again, THANK YOU!
